The South-South Zonal Coordinator of Economic and Financial Crime Commission (EFCC) Mr Nnaghe Obono Itam said the zone has so far recovered a sum of N220m from the zone in five months. Mr Itam who spoke in a press briefing in Port Harcourt yesterday said the zone received about 166 cases within the period, adding that some of the cases were being prosecuted while some convictions have been secured. He said some prominent politicians, including Secretary to Rivers State Government, were taken to court on issues that had to do with financial crime. “We have secured some conviction,” he said